				<text>5.3.2.2 Amplitude, period and frequency</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Write down the amplitude, period and frequency of the function \[h = {@a@}\sin({@b@}t + {@c@})\]</p>
<p>\(\text{amplitude} \quad A = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>\(\text{period}, \qquad T =\) [[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]] (Keep 2 decimal places)</p>
<p>\(\text{frequency} \quad f = \) [[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]] (Keep 2 decimal places)</p>
<p></p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the function \[h = {@a@}\sin({@b@}t + {@c@})\]</p>
<p>The amplitude is \(A = {@a@}\)</p>
<p>The period is \(T = \dfrac{2\pi}{{@b@}} = {@dispdp(2*%pi/b,10)@} ={@dispdp(tb,2)@}\)</p>
<p>The frequency is \(f = \dfrac{1}{T} = {@1/tb@} = {@dispdp(tc,2)@}\)</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
